navigators in the mid 17 th century identify the islands as vietnamese unquestionably vietnam has had long historical relationship with the truong sa_islands their history of_occupation utilization of_resources and_administrative control over the archipelago has its earliest recordings in the 1600 but presence on the chain likely began well before this documentation beyond simple occupation vietnam points to its historical exercise of_control and authority over the island chain the first recorded instance of_this formal sovereignty was the placement of_the island group under the administrative authority of the_binh son_district in the 1600 the pre-colonial vietnamese governments continued to exercise the official unchallenged control of_the archipelago for the next two state the spratly islands vietnam in the 1930 france claimed the_spratly and_paracel islands on behalf of_its then-colony vietnam this french annexation of_the islands provides modern validation
